Three people suspected of killing a boda boda operator were lynched on Tuesday in Kameji village, Rongo subcounty. The three and another suspect are said to have killed Evance Onyango. Their houses were also torched. Youths trailed them from the scene of crime and killed them one after the other. Subcounty commissioner Joseph Satia said the first suspect Erick Otieno was found still wearing bloodstained clothes in his house. &ldquo;The mob attacked him,&rdquo; he said. The mob then went after Erick Ochieng and David Odhiambo. Jacob Ombete escaped. Migori county police commander David Kirui said they are investigating and will arrest the culprits and bring them to justice. The two officers spoke in Rongo town during a security meeting.